The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 CLSA raises stake in LIC arm

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT 

 Mumbai, July 19: CLSA has raised its holding in LIC Housing Finance. 

 CLSA Capital and CLSA Merchant Bankers today informed the stock exchanges that they have acquired 7.27 lakh shares in LIC Housing Finance. The deal will raise their stake to 5.21 per cent.

 CLSA Capital, along with CLSA (Mauritius) Ltd and Calyon, has bought the shares aggregating to 0.86 per cent of the total paid-up capital of LIC Housing Finance.

 While CLSA Mauritius Ltd has acquired 5 lakh shares (0.59 per cent), the rest was bought by CLSA Capital Ltd. The mode of acquisition was open purchase and the transaction took place on July 13.

 CLSA (Mauritius) Limited, CLSA Capital Ltd and Calyon are legally parties acting in concert since they are registered as sub-accounts under the FII registration of CLSA Merchant Bankers Limited and part of the Credit Agricole Group of Companies.

 LIC Housing Finance is the second largest housing finance company in India with a wide marketing network.

 On the BSE today, the LIC Housing Finance scrip ended lower at Rs 232.55 after opening at Rs 239.45.




